data.text:
Raquel Torres O'Brien, hails from picturesque Burgos, Spain. She

brings a passion for service and astute business skills to the

forefront assisting her clients in property transactions.

Raquel holds both a degree in Advertising and Public Relations

(Madrid) and an MBA (US). The twining of both experiences has

led Raquel to unique perspectives linked to both Europe and The

United States.

Holding a great love of wine, Raquel has been very active in

several segments of the wine industry. This stems from her

familyâs ownership of a vineyard nestled in the heart of the

revered Ribera del Duero wine region. These experiences have

lended themselves to reinforcing true standards of the real estate

industry.

Acting as sommelier and wine director at some of Washington,

D.C.'s most prestigious restaurants (Fabio Trabocchi's Del Mar

and Enrique Limardo's Imperfecto) has afforded Raquel great

experience in developing a keen ability to impart invaluable

insight and advice while listening to clientsâ needs. This is a

critical skill in real estate and something that Raquel excels at.

Also invaluable in the real estate industry are cultivated

relationships. In addition to her work as sommelier and director,

Raquel launched her own wine consulting company and is a

member of Women of Wine, a non-profit organization dedicated to

empowering women in the wine community. She has extensive

experience in forming connections and is adept at linking clients

with the right people. This makes her a valuable asset in the

competitive real estate industry.

By merging her commitment to service excellence with her

entrepreneurial acumen, Raquel superbly assists her clients in

achieving their real estate aspirations.

When she's not immersed in the world of real estate, Raquel

resides in Washington, D.C., with her husband and one-year-old

daughter. In her leisure moments, she indulges in her love for

travel, frequently returning to Spain to visit her family while

exploring the country's most exquisite wineries and vineyards.
